		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
		
		
		<div>If they use the personality of the character as a hard template for casting the actor, we're going to end up with live-action NGE starring Jake Lloyd.<br />
<br />
About the only things Daniel Radcliffe would have going for him in this part are his age and his hair, which is, of course, enough for the internet rumor hounds to sink their teeth into it. I find it extremely unlikely that Radcliffe will even be seriously considered for the part, seeing as he has a couple of big drawbacks, not the least of which being his commitment to the Harry Potter films.<br />
<br />
Any rumors circulating about casting now are almost pointless, considering all we've seen is a press release and some concept art from WETA. There isn't even a director yet, let alone serious effort towards casting.<br />
<br />
When the time comes, more than likely we will see a stable of lesser-known or first-time actors involved in this project, which is anything but bad, considering what Lord of the Rings became.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
