</div>
<br />
Being a &quot;dubbie&quot; myself, I would have to disagree with the &quot;characters who are clearly Japanese&quot;. They're drawn to be (or at least appear) caucasian, and when you see them with their voices in the dub, they're more or less Americanized. Though, with Eva, I suppose there is a host of Japanese culture references, even in the dub.<br />
<br />
I'd prefer to see a mixed international cast myself, but for me, Shinji isn't one of the characters that would go over too well as a non-caucasian.<br />
<br />
As far as I'm concerned, the only given for this project so far is that the special effects will be worth the name of the series. WETA won't disappoint, though the rest of the film still might.</div>
	</td>
